1
00:00:01,101 --> 00:00:02,402
♪

2
00:00:02,469 --> 00:00:05,238
Leorio: Please help save gon!

3
00:00:05,305 --> 00:00:06,339
Use your heads!

4
00:00:06,406 --> 00:00:08,241
If you have an idea, do it!

5
00:00:08,308 --> 00:00:11,411
tell me how
I can save him, please.

6
00:00:11,478 --> 00:00:13,046
I’ll do it.

7
00:00:14,114 --> 00:00:15,282
♪

8
00:00:15,349 --> 00:00:17,284
( Singing in Japanese )

9
00:00:43,644 --> 00:00:47,815
♪ You can smile again

10
00:00:47,881 --> 00:00:50,083
( singing in Japanese )

11
00:00:50,150 --> 00:00:53,754
♪ You can fly away

12
00:00:53,820 --> 00:00:55,755
( singing in Japanese )

13
00:00:59,259 --> 00:01:01,128
♪

14
00:01:11,138 --> 00:01:12,806
Narrator: The results
of the eighth round

15
00:01:12,873 --> 00:01:18,145
of elections are in, having been
painstakingly counted by beans.

16
00:01:18,212 --> 00:01:21,415
piyon: I am happy
to finally present the results

17
00:01:21,481 --> 00:01:24,551
of the eighth election
for the 13th chairman!

18
00:01:24,618 --> 00:01:26,153
( Fanfare plays )

19
00:01:26,220 --> 00:01:28,122
( Crowd gasping, murmuring )

20
00:01:29,623 --> 00:01:30,557
Piyon: Oh, wow!

21
00:01:30,624 --> 00:01:33,127
This puts leorio in first place!

22
00:01:33,193 --> 00:01:35,195
That makes it the first time
it’s been someone

23
00:01:35,262 --> 00:01:36,764
other than pariston in the lead!

24
00:01:36,830 --> 00:01:39,333
Leorio got the most votes,

25
00:01:39,399 --> 00:01:43,169
but he only got
44.4% of all votes cast.

26
00:01:43,237 --> 00:01:46,273
The requirement was 50,
which means, of course,

27
00:01:46,340 --> 00:01:49,577
that we’ll have a runoff
between the top two candidates.

28
00:01:49,643 --> 00:01:52,779
( Fanfare continues )

29
00:01:52,846 --> 00:01:54,381
Leorio: Seriously?

30
00:01:54,448 --> 00:01:56,784
Then i’ll really do
whatever I want.

31
00:01:56,850 --> 00:01:59,353
♪

32
00:02:06,393 --> 00:02:09,129
( Ging snoring )

33
00:02:09,196 --> 00:02:11,498
♪

34
00:02:24,211 --> 00:02:26,513
- ( Monitor beeping )
- ( Ventilator hissing )

35
00:02:35,789 --> 00:02:37,691
( Alluka murmuring )

36
00:02:47,634 --> 00:02:49,736
Ah. Hi, big brother.

37
00:02:50,838 --> 00:02:51,772
Killua: Good morning.

38
00:02:51,839 --> 00:02:53,541
Did you sleep well?

39
00:02:53,607 --> 00:02:54,741
Alluka: Uh-huh.

40
00:02:56,710 --> 00:02:58,312
Where are we?

41
00:02:58,378 --> 00:03:00,113
Killua: At a hospital.

42
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:03,283
A friend of mine is here,
and he’s really sick.

43
00:03:03,350 --> 00:03:04,685
( Alluka sighs )

44
00:03:07,287 --> 00:03:10,724
killua: If I can,
I want to help him feel better.

45
00:03:10,791 --> 00:03:12,793
That’s why we’re here.

46
00:03:18,832 --> 00:03:21,201
Alluka: So I have
to switch with nanika?

47
00:03:24,505 --> 00:03:28,242
No fair! I never get to spend
any time with you!

48
00:03:28,308 --> 00:03:30,744
Killua: Look, it’ll be fine.
Don’t worry yourself.

49
00:03:30,811 --> 00:03:34,081
We’re always gonna be
together from now on,

50
00:03:34,147 --> 00:03:35,615
and that’s a promise.

51
00:03:40,854 --> 00:03:42,155
Please.

52
00:03:45,259 --> 00:03:48,062
Illumi: So the rules
don’t apply to killua.

53
00:03:48,128 --> 00:03:50,063
I suspected as much.

54
00:03:50,130 --> 00:03:53,467
i’ll have to check
whether it’s specific to killua,

55
00:03:53,534 --> 00:03:55,669
or perhaps it’s
just something that happens

56
00:03:55,736 --> 00:03:58,472
after a wish is used to heal.

57
00:03:58,539 --> 00:04:01,208
Alluka: Okay. I’ll do it.

58
00:04:01,275 --> 00:04:04,779
illumi: Either way,
the power to destroy and heal

59
00:04:04,845 --> 00:04:09,183
can be a powerful tool
if it’s kept on a short leash.

60
00:04:13,287 --> 00:04:16,023
Tsubone: Sinister and
mechanical, that one,

61
00:04:16,089 --> 00:04:19,793
a wicked ambition contrary
even to the assassin’s creed.

62
00:04:22,396 --> 00:04:25,599
the boy suffered less
when he was being controlled.

63
00:04:25,666 --> 00:04:29,069
How ironic and cruel.

64
00:04:29,136 --> 00:04:31,038
♪

65
00:04:49,156 --> 00:04:53,694
Killua: Alluka is only awake
when nanika’s asleep.

66
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:57,364
She spends less time as alluka
than you’d think.

67
00:04:57,431 --> 00:05:00,701
After one of nanika’s demands
fails and people die,

68
00:05:00,767 --> 00:05:04,571
alluka is awake until nanika
makes the next level-one demand.

69
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:11,778
If the person nanika is making
demands of leaves her side,

70
00:05:11,845 --> 00:05:13,447
the demand is put on hold,

71
00:05:13,514 --> 00:05:16,584
and alluka wakes up
until that person comes back.

72
00:05:18,252 --> 00:05:20,654
after nanika
heals someone or something,

73
00:05:20,721 --> 00:05:22,389
she goes to sleep.

74
00:05:22,456 --> 00:05:25,059
Then alluka is awake
until the next wish.

75
00:05:30,397 --> 00:05:32,733
I want to make
this wish the last

76
00:05:32,799 --> 00:05:35,669
so nanika
will never awaken again.

77
00:05:35,736 --> 00:05:38,339
that would be
the best thing for everyone.

78
00:05:41,141 --> 00:05:43,076
- ( Monitor beeping )
- ( Ventilator hissing )

79
00:06:00,694 --> 00:06:03,297
Nanika: Hand. Hand.

80
00:06:30,624 --> 00:06:32,226
( Teeth grind )

81
00:06:40,334 --> 00:06:42,503
Killua: Please, nanika.

82
00:06:42,569 --> 00:06:45,472
Please heal my friend gon!

83
00:06:45,539 --> 00:06:47,274
Nanika: ’kay.

84
00:06:47,341 --> 00:06:50,044
♪

85
00:07:08,095 --> 00:07:09,597
( Chorus vocalizing )

86
00:07:30,851 --> 00:07:32,619
Morel: Such incredible power.

87
00:07:34,121 --> 00:07:35,656
What’s happening...

88
00:07:35,722 --> 00:07:39,259
And who the hell is doing it?

89
00:07:39,326 --> 00:07:40,661
( Vocalizing continues )

90
00:08:01,081 --> 00:08:03,417
mizaistom:
What the hell was that?

91
00:08:03,483 --> 00:08:07,420
Cheadle: I’ve never felt
anything like this before.

92
00:08:07,487 --> 00:08:10,423
Leorio: Seriously? Seriously?

93
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:13,026
Then i’m just gonna do
whatever I want.

94
00:08:14,194 --> 00:08:16,496
( Vocalizing continues )

95
00:08:25,405 --> 00:08:26,706
♪

96
00:08:44,791 --> 00:08:46,726
( Illumi laughing )

97
00:08:46,793 --> 00:08:49,429
♪

98
00:08:49,496 --> 00:08:51,331
Ah, it’s magnificent!

99
00:08:52,432 --> 00:08:55,335
( Laughing )

100
00:09:03,777 --> 00:09:05,679
- ( Laughter continues )
- ( Thinking ) I want this.

101
00:09:05,746 --> 00:09:08,115
I want this power.

102
00:09:08,182 --> 00:09:11,519
This belongs to me.

103
00:09:11,585 --> 00:09:13,520
( Laughing )

104
00:09:22,095 --> 00:09:23,563
Piyon: If there’s nothing else,

105
00:09:23,630 --> 00:09:25,332
i’ll ask
the two remaining candidates

106
00:09:25,399 --> 00:09:27,568
if they have anything else
they want to say.

107
00:09:27,634 --> 00:09:29,703
And if they don’t, then I guess

108
00:09:29,770 --> 00:09:32,539
we’ll just have to proceed
with the final vote, so...

109
00:09:34,441 --> 00:09:36,176
Cheadle: It’s futile.

110
00:09:36,243 --> 00:09:39,379
It doesn’t matter
what you have to say.

111
00:09:39,446 --> 00:09:42,816
Pariston: Well, it feels
like we’re winding down here,

112
00:09:42,883 --> 00:09:45,586
but I have one more question
for Mr. Leorio.

113
00:09:45,652 --> 00:09:47,287
Leorio: Hmm?

114
00:09:47,354 --> 00:09:48,789
pariston: It’s one
that you’ve answered before.

115
00:09:48,856 --> 00:09:52,593
what will you do
if you become the chairman?

116
00:09:52,659 --> 00:09:56,663
piyon: Mr. Leorio,
kindly answer the question.

117
00:09:56,730 --> 00:10:00,067
what will you do
if you become the chairman?

118
00:10:00,133 --> 00:10:02,402
Leorio: I’m gonna save gon,

119
00:10:02,469 --> 00:10:05,172
and you’ll help,
whether you like it or not!

120
00:10:06,273 --> 00:10:07,407
That’s all.

121
00:10:07,474 --> 00:10:10,110
♪

122
00:10:10,177 --> 00:10:14,081
Pariston: This would have
been perfect timing.

123
00:10:14,147 --> 00:10:17,417
oh, well.
I’m not god, but I tried.

124
00:10:18,485 --> 00:10:19,720
All right,

125
00:10:19,786 --> 00:10:22,255
then, do you have plans
to shuffle personnel

126
00:10:22,322 --> 00:10:24,291
or restructure
the whole organization?

127
00:10:24,358 --> 00:10:27,728
Leorio: Huh? I don’t know
what you’re talking about!

128
00:10:27,794 --> 00:10:30,630
i don’t even know why
i’m standing up here right now.

129
00:10:30,697 --> 00:10:32,232
This crap is ridiculous!

130
00:10:32,299 --> 00:10:34,168
( Pariston laughs )

131
00:10:34,234 --> 00:10:36,203
I couldn’t agree more.
thank you.

132
00:10:36,270 --> 00:10:37,838
those are
all the questions I have.

133
00:10:37,905 --> 00:10:41,342
cheadle: Oh,
just give it up, pariston.

134
00:10:41,408 --> 00:10:43,277
Everyone knew the answers
to those questions

135
00:10:43,343 --> 00:10:45,445
when they voted
for him the first time.

136
00:10:45,512 --> 00:10:48,382
That’s why they were applauding,

137
00:10:48,448 --> 00:10:50,283
because they have
every intention of backing him,

138
00:10:50,350 --> 00:10:51,852
no matter what.

139
00:10:51,919 --> 00:10:53,487
pariston:
Now that we’re talking,

140
00:10:53,554 --> 00:10:55,423
do you have
any more questions for me?

141
00:10:55,489 --> 00:10:56,757
Leorio: Hell, no!

142
00:10:56,823 --> 00:10:58,625
Except why don’t we
just get this over with?

143
00:10:58,692 --> 00:11:00,260
Pariston: I understand,

144
00:11:00,327 --> 00:11:04,198
but i’m afraid I must ask
for an emergency motion!

145
00:11:04,264 --> 00:11:07,501
( Crowd murmuring )

146
00:11:07,568 --> 00:11:08,602
Piyon: Huh?

147
00:11:08,669 --> 00:11:11,705
What is that, exactly?

148
00:11:11,772 --> 00:11:13,207
Pariston: An emergency motion.

149
00:11:13,273 --> 00:11:15,242
Look in the bylaws.

150
00:11:15,309 --> 00:11:18,479
Both articles eight and nine
say that it’s permissible

151
00:11:18,545 --> 00:11:20,814
for me to call
for a vote of confidence.

152
00:11:20,881 --> 00:11:22,683
The topic will be a revision

153
00:11:22,749 --> 00:11:25,652
of the hunter bylaws
and the hunter exam.

154
00:11:25,719 --> 00:11:27,788
but, first,
I propose that we abolish

155
00:11:27,855 --> 00:11:29,623
the current hunter exam system.

156
00:11:29,690 --> 00:11:30,824
( Kanzai growls )

157
00:11:30,891 --> 00:11:32,726
Pariston: If you agree,
please vote yea.

158
00:11:32,793 --> 00:11:35,195
Disagree, and vote nay.

159
00:11:35,262 --> 00:11:36,530
Kanzai: Hold it right there!

160
00:11:36,597 --> 00:11:38,566
During the zodiac council,

161
00:11:38,632 --> 00:11:41,135
we decided the bylaws
wouldn’t be touched!

162
00:11:41,201 --> 00:11:44,538
So that isn’t relevant
right now, and you know it!

163
00:11:44,605 --> 00:11:45,739
Saccho: No.

164
00:11:45,806 --> 00:11:48,542
Cheadle: Stupid tiger.
you’re wrong.

165
00:11:48,609 --> 00:11:50,444
Pariston: Absolutely right!

166
00:11:50,511 --> 00:11:53,581
The council’s decision
was 11 to 1.

167
00:11:53,647 --> 00:11:57,451
i was the only one
in favor of revising the bylaws.

168
00:11:57,518 --> 00:12:02,056
If instead miss cheadle or
Mr. Mizaistom were up here now,

169
00:12:02,122 --> 00:12:03,590
i’d have stayed silent,

170
00:12:03,657 --> 00:12:07,094
deferring to the wisdom
of the council for the duration,

171
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:09,663
but both of them
are out of the running,

172
00:12:09,730 --> 00:12:12,800
and, as you all heard
Mr. Leorio clearly state,

173
00:12:12,866 --> 00:12:15,502
he has no plans
for the association.

174
00:12:15,569 --> 00:12:17,337
This is the only time

175
00:12:17,404 --> 00:12:19,840
I can express my opinion
as vice chairman

176
00:12:19,907 --> 00:12:22,510
and not just
as one of the zodiacs,

177
00:12:22,576 --> 00:12:23,811
my one opportunity.

178
00:12:23,877 --> 00:12:26,413
Understand, Mr. Kanzai?

179
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:29,183
Right here and right now,

180
00:12:29,249 --> 00:12:31,418
it’s the only chance
that i’ll ever get!

181
00:12:31,485 --> 00:12:32,820
( Crowd murmuring )

182
00:12:32,886 --> 00:12:34,821
( Kanzai sputters )

183
00:12:34,888 --> 00:12:37,758
Pariston: Of course,
according to article eight,

184
00:12:37,824 --> 00:12:41,261
I could ignore the council’s
decision and force the motion,

185
00:12:41,328 --> 00:12:44,832
but, even though it’s my right,
I really don’t want to do that.

186
00:12:44,898 --> 00:12:50,237
The zodiacs are a precious
legacy left by the chairman!

187
00:12:50,304 --> 00:12:52,840
piyon: Hey,
if you say something stupid,

188
00:12:52,906 --> 00:12:55,275
he’s gonna make this
ten times worse.

189
00:12:55,342 --> 00:12:56,443
( Kanzai groans )

190
00:12:56,510 --> 00:12:58,812
Pariston: Honestly,
part of me wishes

191
00:12:58,879 --> 00:13:02,316
to let this matter die
without making any more waves.

192
00:13:02,382 --> 00:13:05,485
However, the late Mr. Teradein
and Mr. Bushidora

193
00:13:05,552 --> 00:13:08,388
made an excellent point
before they passed.

194
00:13:08,455 --> 00:13:13,193
Both articles three and four
continue to suffer gravely

195
00:13:13,260 --> 00:13:16,196
as a direct result
of the current exam process!

196
00:13:16,263 --> 00:13:18,198
cheadle:
"He doesn’t want to win,

197
00:13:18,265 --> 00:13:20,434
but he doesn’t want
to lose, either."

198
00:13:20,501 --> 00:13:23,604
I have to say, ging,
looks like you’re right.

199
00:13:23,670 --> 00:13:26,306
What a creep.

200
00:13:26,373 --> 00:13:30,110
he doesn’t care
about winning or losing at all,

201
00:13:30,177 --> 00:13:32,379
so, with nothing
of his own at risk,

202
00:13:32,446 --> 00:13:34,848
he can always
stay dispassionate and calm

203
00:13:34,915 --> 00:13:38,585
while he manipulates others
and plays the rules against us

204
00:13:38,652 --> 00:13:42,156
in the worst way any of us
could possibly imagine.

205
00:13:46,793 --> 00:13:48,328
May I say something?

206
00:13:48,395 --> 00:13:50,397
Piyon: Yes? What is it?

207
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:56,170
Cheadle: If leorio
is elected chairman,

208
00:13:56,236 --> 00:13:58,305
I volunteer to be his advisor.

209
00:13:58,372 --> 00:14:00,774
at that point,
I promise that I will conduct

210
00:14:00,841 --> 00:14:04,278
a comprehensive review
of the bylaws and hunter exam.

211
00:14:04,344 --> 00:14:08,481
I will not let you grab
any of teradein’s votes.

212
00:14:08,549 --> 00:14:12,386
i’ll destroy
every last argument you make.

213
00:14:12,452 --> 00:14:16,389
To everyone who’s voting
for the potential leorio shows,

214
00:14:16,456 --> 00:14:19,225
but who’s concerned about
how he will serve initially,

215
00:14:19,293 --> 00:14:22,329
I will do everything I can
to quell those concerns,

216
00:14:22,396 --> 00:14:24,565
even if it requires me
to leave the zodiacs.

217
00:14:24,631 --> 00:14:26,199
Leorio: Wait a minute!

218
00:14:26,266 --> 00:14:28,068
i don’t know what
you guys are talking about,

219
00:14:28,135 --> 00:14:30,137
but i’m in a hurry
to go save gon

220
00:14:30,204 --> 00:14:31,772
as quickly as I can!

221
00:14:34,641 --> 00:14:36,409
Morel: Leorio!

222
00:14:36,476 --> 00:14:39,379
♪

223
00:15:18,352 --> 00:15:20,287
♪

224
00:16:03,830 --> 00:16:06,733
Leorio: Gon!

225
00:16:10,437 --> 00:16:14,374
( Wails )

226
00:16:14,441 --> 00:16:16,176
D-damn it!

227
00:16:16,243 --> 00:16:19,146
I was so worried about you!

228
00:16:24,451 --> 00:16:27,688
Gon: Leorio!

229
00:16:27,754 --> 00:16:30,357
♪

230
00:16:33,660 --> 00:16:35,595
Leorio: I’m so glad!

231
00:16:35,662 --> 00:16:40,200
You--you have no idea!

232
00:16:42,135 --> 00:16:44,337
Gon: Was it really
all that bad?

233
00:16:44,404 --> 00:16:47,407
( Leorio laughs ) Bad doesn’t
even begin to cover it!

234
00:16:47,474 --> 00:16:49,409
morel: Leorio,
knock it off, will you?

235
00:16:49,476 --> 00:16:52,579
isn’t it enough
that he’s healed, already?

236
00:16:52,646 --> 00:16:54,381
Leorio: Yeah, you’re right.

237
00:16:54,448 --> 00:16:56,583
( Chuckling )

238
00:16:58,685 --> 00:17:00,420
( Gon gasps )

239
00:17:00,487 --> 00:17:02,322
( Crowd applauding )

240
00:17:11,198 --> 00:17:12,366
( Leorio chuckles ) See?

241
00:17:12,432 --> 00:17:15,368
Everybody in here
was worried about you.

242
00:17:15,435 --> 00:17:18,371
Gon: Uh, thanks! Thank you.

243
00:17:18,438 --> 00:17:21,341
Cheadle: He got us.

244
00:17:21,408 --> 00:17:25,245
Pariston wanted leorio
to be his final opponent.

245
00:17:26,446 --> 00:17:29,382
and now leorio
has neither the motive

246
00:17:29,449 --> 00:17:32,185
nor the support
to become the next chairman.

247
00:17:32,252 --> 00:17:34,221
Man: You be chairman!

248
00:17:34,288 --> 00:17:37,792
morel: Leorio,
we know that killua healed gon,

249
00:17:37,858 --> 00:17:40,461
but you can never
tell gon that.

250
00:17:40,527 --> 00:17:41,795
Leorio: Huh? Why not?

251
00:17:41,862 --> 00:17:43,797
Morel: ’cause I said so.

252
00:17:43,864 --> 00:17:47,835
For killua’s sake,
keep it to yourself.

253
00:17:47,901 --> 00:17:49,770
Leorio: Right. Yeah.

254
00:17:49,837 --> 00:17:51,372
It’s our secret.

255
00:17:52,639 --> 00:17:54,508
Cheadle: Tell me, pariston.

256
00:17:54,575 --> 00:17:56,310
I’m curious.

257
00:17:56,376 --> 00:17:59,813
When did you first predict that
this would be the final outcome?

258
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:02,516
Pariston: Pardon? Oh, no, no.

259
00:18:02,583 --> 00:18:05,052
I don’t have the ability
to predict things.

260
00:18:05,118 --> 00:18:07,520
This was all pure coincidence.

261
00:18:10,457 --> 00:18:12,626
Cheadle: Please. I want to know.

262
00:18:14,127 --> 00:18:15,495
That was a...

263
00:18:15,562 --> 00:18:17,330
Total defeat.

264
00:18:22,169 --> 00:18:23,570
Pariston: I realized it...

265
00:18:23,637 --> 00:18:26,773
When Mr. Ging nominated himself.

266
00:18:26,840 --> 00:18:28,141
Cheadle: Huh?

267
00:18:28,208 --> 00:18:29,710
pariston:
After he said he would run,

268
00:18:29,776 --> 00:18:32,345
I asked a question to taunt him,

269
00:18:32,412 --> 00:18:36,283
and he responded by saying
that gon wouldn’t die, right?

270
00:18:36,350 --> 00:18:40,654
ging: Nah, go.
That kid’s not gonna die.

271
00:18:42,189 --> 00:18:44,525
Pariston: Right there
in that moment,

272
00:18:44,591 --> 00:18:48,762
I could visualize the scene
that just transpired before us.

273
00:18:50,364 --> 00:18:54,568
I anticipated Mr. Ging and I
would stand onstage

274
00:18:54,635 --> 00:18:57,104
and that he
would ultimately win,

275
00:18:57,171 --> 00:18:58,839
in my vision, at least.

276
00:18:58,906 --> 00:19:00,107
Cheadle: Huh.

277
00:19:00,174 --> 00:19:02,043
Pariston: First, since Mr. Ging

278
00:19:02,109 --> 00:19:05,512
seemed confident that gon would
survive, I began to suspect

279
00:19:05,579 --> 00:19:08,048
that there must be
some way he could be healed.

280
00:19:08,115 --> 00:19:12,620
I also realized that if he
became part of the election,

281
00:19:12,686 --> 00:19:15,255
I would never be able to win.

282
00:19:15,322 --> 00:19:16,290
( Cheadle gasps )

283
00:19:16,356 --> 00:19:17,657
Pariston: Understand?

284
00:19:17,724 --> 00:19:22,229
you see, that was
the exact moment I was defeated.

285
00:19:23,730 --> 00:19:26,333
but Mr. Ging
withdrew from the election,

286
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:30,204
and, soon after, Mr. Leorio
showed up and punched him.

287
00:19:30,270 --> 00:19:33,206
When he stood onstage
and talked about his friends

288
00:19:33,273 --> 00:19:36,777
risking their lives
to save gon, it all clicked.

289
00:19:36,844 --> 00:19:40,348
I finally saw the bigger picture
for what it was,

290
00:19:40,414 --> 00:19:44,184
but it was only a moment ago
that I knew I had won,

291
00:19:44,251 --> 00:19:47,354
when we felt
that immense power.

292
00:19:47,421 --> 00:19:52,559
I had a gut feeling that gon’s
friends had just saved him.

293
00:19:52,626 --> 00:19:57,097
All that remained was to delay
the vote until he arrived.

294
00:19:57,164 --> 00:20:00,334
Oh, and don’t worry.
I’ll retract my motion.

295
00:20:01,869 --> 00:20:04,572
Cheadle: And that was
all the information you had?

296
00:20:04,638 --> 00:20:09,843
You trusted people you’d never
even met to save gon? Seriously?

297
00:20:13,547 --> 00:20:16,683
Pariston: I trust Mr. Ging
as a worthy enemy,

298
00:20:16,750 --> 00:20:18,218
( cheadle gasps )

299
00:20:18,285 --> 00:20:20,420
Pariston: And these are
the very same friends

300
00:20:20,487 --> 00:20:23,156
that Mr. Ging trusted
to save his son...

301
00:20:24,391 --> 00:20:25,359
So I did, too.

302
00:20:26,627 --> 00:20:28,262
I’d be foolish not to.

303
00:20:38,572 --> 00:20:39,706
( Crowd cheering )

304
00:20:39,773 --> 00:20:41,708
man: Come on!
Run for chairman already!

305
00:20:41,775 --> 00:20:44,511
Man 2: You’d be awesome!
you got my vote!

306
00:20:44,578 --> 00:20:47,548
Man 3: Get onstage,
and say something!

307
00:20:47,614 --> 00:20:49,316
Man 4: Speech! Speech!

308
00:20:49,383 --> 00:20:52,553
gon: Aw, man,
I don’t know what to do.

309
00:20:52,619 --> 00:20:53,687
( Gasps )

310
00:21:04,731 --> 00:21:06,266
( Cheering fades )

311
00:21:09,603 --> 00:21:10,637
Gon: Ging?

312
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:15,409
( Ging grunts )

313
00:21:15,475 --> 00:21:16,843
This is bad.

314
00:21:18,445 --> 00:21:23,283
But I guess I always knew
this was gonna happen.

315
00:21:23,350 --> 00:21:25,285
♪

316
00:21:30,891 --> 00:21:32,826
( Singing in Japanese )

